#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:2
msgid "Installing the OS"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:4
msgid "**Required Components**"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:6
msgid "Raspberry Pi 4B/Zero 2 w/3B 3B+/2B/Zero W"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:7
msgid "1 x Personal Computer"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:8
msgid "1 x Micro SD card"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:10
msgid "**Steps**"
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:13
msgid "Go to the Raspberry Pi software download page: `Raspberry Pi Imager <https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/>`_. Select the Imager version for your operating system. After downloading, open the file to start the installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:18
msgid "Upon launching the installer, your OS might display a security warning. For instance, Windows may show a caution message. If this occurs, select **More info** and then **Run anyway**. Follow the on-screen instructions to install the Raspberry Pi Imager."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:23
msgid "Insert your SD card into the computer or laptop SD card slot."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:25
msgid "Open the Raspberry Pi Imager application either by clicking its icon or executing ``rpi-imager`` in your terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:29
msgid "Click **CHOOSE DEVICE** and select your specific Raspberry Pi model from the list (Note: Raspberry Pi 5 is not applicable)."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:33
msgid "Select **CHOOSE OS** and then choose **Raspberry Pi OS (Legacy)**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:36
msgid "Please do not install the **Bookworm** version as the speaker will not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:37
msgid "You need to install the **Raspberry Pi OS (Legacy)** version - **Debian Bullseye**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:42
msgid "Click **Choose Storage** and pick the correct storage device for the installation."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:46
msgid "Be sure to select the correct device, especially if multiple storage devices are connected. Disconnect others if you're unsure."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:50
msgid "Press **NEXT** and select **EDIT SETTINGS** to customize your OS settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:54
msgid "Set your Raspberry Pi's **hostname**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:58
msgid "The hostname is what your Raspberry Pi uses to identify itself on the network. You can connect to your Pi using `<hostname>.local` or `<hostname>.lan`."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:62
msgid "Create a **Username** and **Password** for the Raspberry Pi's administrator account."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:66
msgid "Setting a unique username and password is crucial for security, as the Raspberry Pi does not have a default password."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:70
msgid "Set up wireless LAN by inputting your network's **SSID** and **Password**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:74
msgid "``Wireless LAN country`` should be set the two-letter `ISO/IEC alpha2 code <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-2#Officially_assigned_code_elements>`_ for the country in which you are using your Raspberry Pi."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:79
msgid "Click **SERVICES** and enable **SSH** for password-based remote access. Remember to click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:83
msgid "Confirm your choices by clicking **Yes**."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:87
msgid "If your SD card has existing files, back them up to avoid data loss. Click **Yes** to proceed if no backup is necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../python_start/installing_the_os.rst:91
msgid "Wait as the OS is written to the SD card. Once completed, a confirmation window will appear."
msgstr ""
